      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Do you test it ? because I&#39;ve just wrote a program java and the string  <code>&quot;        string, with , space    &quot;.trim()</code> return <code>&quot;string, with , space&quot;</code>. Like javadoc says : returns a copy of the string, with leading and trailing whitespace omitted. You are wrong and @user872858 is right."
